# Git for Windows enables core.autocrlf in its system config, so a plain
# clone there would rewrite every working-tree file to CRLF. Those files are
# exactly what Stow symlinks into $HOME and what POSIX tools then read, so
# pin LF and keep checkouts byte-identical on every platform.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Windows-native files already stored with CRLF in the index. -text disables
# EOL conversion outright, so `git add --renormalize` leaves their bytes
# alone; they still diff as text.
win/wsl/.wslconfig -text
win/wsl/mount.vbs -text
